    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.231.100894.figure104>
    dc:description "Figure 104. Solanum nitidibaccatum A habit B fruiting habit C fruiting habit showing leaf variation D detail of adaxial leaf surface E detail of abaxial leaf surface F flower bud G dissected flower H fruit (A, C, F Henning 14 B, D, E, H Blake 186 C Arnow 740). Illustration by R. Wise. Previously published in Saerkinen et al. (2018: 107) and Knapp et al. (2019: 92)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/897565" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.231.100894.figure105>
    dc:description "Figure 105. Solanum nitidibaccatum A habit B young inflorescence with flower buds C flowers at anthesis D maturing fruits (A-D Saerkinen et al. 4076). Photos by T. Saerkinen. Previously published in Saerkinen et al. (2018: 108) and Knapp et al. (2019: 93)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/897566" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.231.100894.figure106>
    dc:description "Figure 106. Distribution map of Solanum nitidibaccatum in South America. For distribution in North and Central America and the Caribbean, see Knapp et al. (2019: 95) and adventive distribution elsewhere, see Saerkinen et al. (2018: 109)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/897567" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

